qas.question: What is the name of the supplement that first appeared in 1902 as a supplement to The Times?
In 1914, a separately paid-for supplement for The Times was a magazine that featured what kind of content?
The editorial offices of The Times Literary Supplement is based in what location in London?
In what year did The Times Literary Supplement begin publishing online?

context: The <a0_0>Times Literary Supplement<a0_0/> (TLS) first appeared in 1902 as a supplement to The Times, becoming a separately paid-for <a1_0>weekly literature<a1_0/> and society magazine in 1914. The Times and the TLS have continued to be co-owned, and as of <a3_0>2012<a3_0/> the TLS is also published by News International and cooperates closely with The Times, with its online version hosted on The Times website, and its editorial offices based in <a2_0>Times House, Pennington Street<a2_0/>, London.
